column60: You have conquered the forest. Now you must build a kingdom worthy of your name.
In a moment of weakness the Marquise descended. Now you have rallied your strength and are poised to recapture you birthright.
You wander the woods, seeking a place in the new society that is taking shape.
The Riverfolk Company are always on the hunt for new markets. After all, where there's muck, there's clams!
Keep your Croco-dial locked for your soundrach to the woodland's demise
The world will end when we get paid.
Your strength rests with us now.
Every supply taken is another day you can survive.
Your brigade has appropriated a rusty cannon. In this new age, the only way to gain sovereignty is through either spray or sulfur.

Your people have been ignored, berated, or bullied by your fellow denizens for far too long. You and your small brigade have approiated a rusty cannon to arm yourselves. The only way to gain the proper respect is through either spray or sulfur.
Rise, sisters! Bring them all chthonic justice.
Give us the bones!
All the chaos, All the time!
We are only here to help.
An unnatural power looms in the darkest corners of the forest, a ribbiting and most ancient mystical authority. Beware the magical might of the abominous amphibians!
Don't tread on us.
Out of nowhere the Old Man appeared with his wondrous automatons. He claims to come from the future, but is the war ravaged woodland he speaks of our fate? Or is he mad?
The confilct in this distant woodland is of vital importance. You must manipulate the outcome to our advantage.
Political power comes only through sacrifice of your ideals.
Scuttle the ship. We have arrived.
This avian empire shall not fall.
Driven by a mandate from heaven, you are on a holy quest to bring this Woodland to the path of righteousness.
You have claimed lordship over this land, but discontent stirs. Apease the masses and fulfill your promises!
Spread your minions through the underbrush, eat the puny warriors of the Woodland, and expand your treasure! Let all tremble in fear before the mighty Wyrm!
War has come to the Woodlands, and it is up to your order to save as many lives as you can!
Pieces must be sacraficed in every game of chess.
Koalas live off eucalyptus and the thrill of gambling.
Our story will be filled with triumph and tragedy - provided no one looks to closely.
The Mountain King's domain has fallen into chaos. Reestablish order before he wakes, lest his ire destroys us all.
Your paws built whatever the tyrant demanded. But now you're free and unified. It's time to tear down the old Woodland and build it right.
You once upheald the law for lethargic royals. But gold on a crown does not make a king - only the gold in their coin purse.
The Chieftans will give you strength.
You might lack a stomach, but your dark order still hungers for woodland domination.
Start off as a popular uprising, become increasingly violent, and end up as tyrannical as the rule you overthrew!
You have conquered the forest. Now you must build a kingdom worthy of your name.

Long hated, long despised, the dark marsupials return to the underwoods. The reek of death reigns the battlefields, the corpses litter the ground, and the we, the Necropussums have come as the dead for a dance...
Build your claim to fame!
The Farmers of Hamstershire want nothing more than to raise their crops and give gifts to their friends.
In the name of the Empress, you lead a massive invasion force to colonize the woodland, and get lots of honey!
The spiders of the forest have awoken from their slumber. The forest is stirring - the small, furry prey have risen against each other in war, and the spiders are hungry. The hunt is on.
The spiders of the forest have awoken from their slumber. The forest is stirring - the small, furry prey have risen against each other in war, and the spiders are hungry. The hunt is on.
The denizens of the Woodland have put their faith in you. For better or worse.
The emperor has set his gaze on new lands. What better way to conquer than to show the wealth and culture of his empire.
After taking care of the sustenance of the woodland creatures, the Cooperative has decided to expand their agricultural empire!
The forest holds many secrets. With clarity, they can become reality.
A coalition of frogs, toads and newts came together to secure a future for their kin.
Resources are disappearing in the forest. It is time to wake up, educate the woodlands, and fight the polluters. By force if necessary.
You wander the woods, finding those like you; working to secure a safe place in this old woodland that is taking new shape.

Verily, in the vast wilderness, the tranquility hath been disrupted, and thou dost seeketh a path to restore harmony. Lo, the riots have spreadeth far and wide, and the season of winter slumber draweth nigh...
All these factions claim to speak for the Woodland while cutting down her trees. You shall show them the real might of the woods...
Disgraced and forced to flee from your kingdom far away, you arrive in the woods at the edge of the coming conflict. Sharpen the spears, patch the wounds - this is a new beginning for the guard.
Your people know that before the Eyrie, the Woodland was your home. Now, you return to a foreign land to fulfill an ancient prophecy - you will rule again.
Grow and spread in the wake of its destruction.
